headline: France's centrists mull fallback presidential candidates
description: While former prime ministers Edouard Philippe and Gabriel Attal are already officially running, some allies of Emmanuel Macron would rather see the president's legacy defended by Jean Castex or Sébastien Lecornu, whom they see as more loyal.

Why Ethiopia and Eritrea are once again on the brink of war
description: Tensions are rising between the two countries and the rebel region of Tigray. Addis Ababa has mobilized troops and artillery along the border of its northern province, while Asmara has drawn closer to the Tigrayan insurgents – a dramatic reversal of alliances.

headline: With 'Orwell: 2+2=5,' Raoul Peck launches a sweeping denunciation of contemporary horrors
description: Haitian filmmaker Raoul Peck's ambitious documentary attempts to pay tribute to George Orwell's visionary novel '1984,' but instead it brings together so many situations that individual nuances ultimately become lost.

headline: Rama Duwaji's committed choices and strong opinions
description: The 28-year-old illustrator has been closely watched by media outlets around the world ever since her husband, Zohran Mamdani, was elected mayor of New York.

headline: Morocco's old colonial wounds reopened by tribute to French army auxiliaries
description: France's recent inauguration of a new military burial plot for 20th-century Moroccan auxiliaries in Morocco's High Atlas has sparked controversy, as these soldiers fought against local resistance fighters before Moroccan independence.

After four years of war in Ukraine, Russia's economy could fall into recession
description: The Russian economy, fueled by the country's military-industrial complex, had long posted growth rates above the European average. Today, however, the country's economic indicators are all in the red.

headline: Understanding the battle of Verdun through rare or little-known photographs
description: A book published to mark the 110th anniversary of the legendary battle brings to light many images taken by army photographers. Le Monde is presenting several of these photographs, offering a glimpse into the reality behind this symbol of the First World War.

headline: Donald Trump's support with 'bro culture' is waning
description: With his racist post about the Obamas, support for immigration police and decision to politicize Puerto Rican singer Bad Bunny's halftime Super Bowl show, the US president has alienated some of his supporters.
